column2: at the river, in the ravine
it went out; it was going out
it is pierced, it is perforated
it is probable, it is possible
he removed it; he took it away
on him, on it, in it
at it, on it, in it
you will take care of me
it was know, it was the custom
woman who has just given birth
it is tied by the corners
you all will go to help me
I will take care of it
it pleased us, we liked it
you grab him by the neck
he grabbed it; he took it
they make food; they prepare meals
he put himself; he lay down
he gives it a name, he baptizes it
it is stuck, it is cemented
